Write a program to accept a comma-separated list of elements from the user, convert it into a tuple, and perform a slicing operation based on two user-provided indices.

SOLUTION:

n=raw_input("Enter elements: ").split(',')
t=tuple(n)
print t
x=int(input("Enter 1st index: "))
y=int(input("Enter 2nd index: "))
print "After slicing: ",t[x:y]
